<DESCRIPT>  AIR; AVIATION; ASSAULT; MIDEAST; IRAQ; KUWAIT; US; WORLD; SAUDI-ARABIA; WAR;
MILITARY; DEFENSE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  President Bush is expected to hear today that U.S. commanders in the Persian
Gulf war want to delay the start of a ground war against Iraq for up to a
month while allied bombers further pound the enemy.;    Defense Secretary Dick
Cheney and Gen. Colin Powell, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, are
expected to deliver that assessment after spending two days in the war zone
getting a report on Operation Desert Storm's progress.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  GROUND WAR MAY BE DELAYED
MILITARY REPORTEDLY WANTS MORE SORTIES  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Mercury News wire services contributed to this report.
War in the Gulf
See also related stories on pages 1A, 10A-11A in this section
